properties.description:
LEAVE NOW: Sunshine Acres bushfire as at 3:30pm Thurs 4 Feb        Bushfire warning level: WATCH AND ACT     Queensland Fire and Emergency Services (QFES) advises there is a bushfire in Sunshine Acres and conditions are getting worse.     Follow your bushfire survival plan now . If you do not have a plan, your safest option is to  leave now  if it is clear to do so. If you are not in the area,  do not return , as conditions are too dangerous.    Currently as at 3:30pm Thursday 4 February, a fast-moving fire is burning in the vicinity of Baxters Road and Black Swamp Creek. The fire is likely to impact Sunshine Acres, as well as Corella Way, Honeyeater Drive and Finch Court, Walligan imminently. The fire could have a significant impact on the community.    Residents on the eastern side of the Maryboroguh Hervey Bay road should evacuate east along the Booral Road towards Booral. Residents on the western side of the Maryborough Hervey Bay road should evacuate west along the Howard Tornbanlea road towards Howard.    Fire crews are working to contain the fire but firefighters may not be able to protect every property. You  should not expect a firefighter at your door . Power, water, and mobile phone service may be lost.    People in the area will be affected by smoke, which will reduce visibility and air quality.    Call Triple Zero (000) immediately if you believe you are under threat. 
Response Time: 20210204132309
